NaturalPoint Trackable Export Data: == First entry of each row identifies row type.
== comment: Comment, you can ignore this information
== info: reports number of trackable definitions and
== trackable: Details rigid body definition in the following format:
==    -- X,Y,Z (float) 3D position of each marker in rigid body
== frame: Details frame of exported data in the following format:
==    -- Trackable Count (integer) number of trackables tracked in current frame
==    -- Trackable ID, Position, Quaternion Orientation, and Eulers Orientation >for each tracked trackable< (ID, x,y,z, qx, qy, qz, qw, yaw, pitch, roll)
==    -- Marker Count (integer) Count of all visibile markers in frame
== trackable: Extended information for current frame:
==    -- Trackable Marker Location >for each marker in trackable< (x,y,z)
==    -- Point Cloud Marker corresponding to each trackable marker (x,y,z). (NAN,NAN,NAN) used for missing Point Cloud Markers.
==    -- Marker Quality (float) for each marker. 1.0=Highest Quality, 0.0=Lowest Quality
== righthanded: Indicates a right-handed coordinate system
== lefthanded: Indicates a left-handed coordinate system
